<br>
Getting exp in an easy zone with almost no loot = boring.<br>
<br>
However, this activity can be combined with quest camps for other guildies, on many occasions... Chardok for Eldwyn's pipe is an excellent example.  No loot ever seems to drop, but the exp is good and there is a benefit to the guild as a whole.<br>
<br>
Getting exp in a tough zone with reasonable loot drops = less boring.<br>
<br>
Good examples of these camps are Upper/Lower Dogs in Velks, most of the camps in Seb, and (I'm told) some of the Karnors Castle camps.<br>
<br>
Everyone likes the chance to roll on an uber drop... but these areas are also a greater challenge and I like the test of our gaming skill.<br>
<br>
Raiding for uber lewtz in negative exp zones = getting pretty interesting.<br>
<br>
Good examples of these are Growthplane and more recently Hateplane... call me greedy but I want my planes armour, and I mean the full set.<br>
<br>
Questing = great fun.<br>
<br>
I started the Kromrif Military Leggings quest on Sunday (and the more advanced questers in the guild will laugh at such a simple quest)... but it takes you to new zones to meet new NPC's and kill new monsters.<br>
<br>
The big raids can only take place when enough ppl are online and willing to do them, so they need advance planning and probably will take place during weekends.  A division between the other areas of activity is likely to be our focus during weekdays.<br>
<br>
Shadowfrost Dawnrazor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#200000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/ubarnabasc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarnabasC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Rat hunter</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/7/01 12:26:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fbloodcultfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What do you think about ...</span><hr size=1> Personally, I have quested very little becuase I considered it mostly a waste of time. Not that I don`t need the quest items, but the exp that I &quot;lost&quot; by camping boring quest camps just didn`t seem worth it. I did do some when I felt that the ned of the item justified the &quot;lost&quot; exp that the time investment required. Examples of this are the Acumen Mask, Staff of Temperate Flux, and the Staff of the Wheel quest. I just always figured that attaining a higher level in the game was much more important, making any quests that I do attempt much easier. <br>
<br>
That having been said, what do I now prefer? I still prefer EXP over pfat lewt. If not for the reason that the quests that I wish to do I am not yet in the position to solo and getting most people motivated enough to really help seems to be very difficult.<br>
